    <thetext>In ES3 and 5 it was an internal method.  I&apos;m hoping that it becomes something else.  Possibly a real method such as @@match, but it could potentially also be a function valued internal data property. 

In either case, I really haven&apos;t work on that problem yet, and the RegExp spec language is still in a transitional state.</thetext>
